obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (83651)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83651&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Dental`
  line `Commission Act, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference`
  line `to the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 29th February, 2024, Sections 4, 5, 6, 8, 10, 11, 17, 19, 40, 41, 53 and 58(5), vide notification No. S.O. 990(E), dated 29th`
  line `February, 2024, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (83652)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83652&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Autonomous Board" means any of the Autonomous Boards constituted under`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the National Dental Commission`
  line `appointed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the National Dental Commission constituted under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "Council" means the Dental Advisory Council constituted under section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) "Dental Assessment and Rating Board" means the Board constituted under`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) "dental auxiliary" includes a dental hygienist or a dental mechanic or a dental`
  line `operating room assistant or such other category as may be specified by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(g) "dental hygienist" means a person not being a dentist or a medical practitioner`
  line `who scales, cleans or polishes teeth, or gives instruction in dental hygiene;`
  line
  line `(h) "dental institution" means any institution within or outside India which grants`
  line `degrees, diplomas, certificates for certification courses or licences in dentistry and`
  line `includes affiliated colleges, deemed to be Universities and institutions mentioned in the`
  line Schedule;
  line
  line `(i) "dental mechanic" means a person qualified to perform laboratory work required`
  line `for the prosthetic rehabilitation of dental and maxillofacial structures and orthodontic`
  line appliances;
  line
  line `(j) "dental operating room assistant" means a person who assists the dentist in`
  line `sterilising and handing over instruments as required by the dentist at the chair side;`
  line
  line `(k) "dentist" means a person who practices dentistry;`
  line
  line `(l) "dentistry" includes the science, practice and research in dental and oral health,`
  line `directed towards--`
  line
  line `(i) facilitating healthy development of dentition, jaws and dentofacial structures;`
  line
  line `(ii) prevention of oral diseases and promotion of oral health;`
  line
  line `(iii) diagnosis and use of diagnostic tests, investigations and procedure to decide`
  line `the normal and abnormal state or diseases of teeth, gums, jaws and related tissues`
  line `necessary for the functions of the oral cavity;`
  line
  line `(iv) performing procedures for the optimisation of dental and oral health, which`
  line `may include restoration, rehabilitation, surgery or a combination thereof, to restore`
  line `the functions, structural anatomy and aesthetics of the stomatognathic system and the`
  line `masticatory apparatus;`
  line
  line `(v) creating awareness and working knowledge of the effects of systemic health`
  line `on dentition and oral cavity and to perform the duties of an active member of the`
  line `healthcare team, including basic life support;`
  line
  line `(vi) promoting good systemic health through diagnosis and necessary`
  line `interventions related to oral health conditions; and`
  line
  line `(vii) bringing awareness of oral health related issues of the society and of nation`
  line `and to facilitate implementation of the updated policies of the Government or`
  line `Government bodies in this regard;`
  line
  line `(m) "Ethics and Dental Registration Board" means the Board constituted under`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(n) "Fund" means the National Dental Commission Fund referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 39;`
  line
  line `(o) "leader" means the Head of a Department or the Head of an Institute or`
  line organisation;
  line
  line `(p) "licence" means a licence to practice dentistry granted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 31;`
  line
  line `(q) "Member" means a Member of the Commission appointed under section 4 and`
  line `includes the Chairperson thereof, or, as the case may be, a Member of the Autonomous`
  line `Board referred to in section 17 and includes the President thereof;`
  line
  line `(r) "National Register" means the National Register for Dentists or the National`
  line `Register for Dental Auxiliaries, as the case may be, maintained by the Ethics and Dental`
  line `Registration Board under section 30;`
  line
  line `(s) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the`
  line `expression "notify" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(t) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(u) "President" means the President of an Autonomous Board appointed under`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(v) "recognised dental qualification" means a dental qualification recognised under`
  line `section 33 or section 34 or section 35, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(w) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Commission under this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) "registered professional" means any dentist or dental auxiliary who is registered in`
  line `the National Register or the State Register under section 30;`
  line
  line `(y) "Schedule" means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(z) "State Dental Council" means a dental council constituted under any law for the`
  line `time being in force in any State or Union territory for regulating the practice and`
  line `registration of practitioners of dentistry in that State or Union territory and includes a Joint`
  line `Dental Council referred to in sub-section (7) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(za) "State Register" means the State Register for Dentists or the State Register for`
  line `Dental Auxiliaries, as the case may be, maintained under any law for the time being in`
  line `force in any State or Union territory for registration of dentists or dental auxiliaries, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(zb) "Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board" means the Board`
  line `constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(zc) "University" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (f) of`
  line `section 2 (3 of 1956) of the University Grants Commission Act, 1956 and includes a`
  line `health University.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (83653)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of National Dental Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83653&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, with effect from such date as it may appoint,`
  line `constitute a Commission, to be known as the National Dental Commission, to exercise the`
  line `powers conferred upon, and to perform the functions assigned to it, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire,`
  line `hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by`
  line `the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Commission shall be at New Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (83654)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83654&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall consist of the following`
  line `persons to be appointed by the Central Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) eight ex officio Members; and`
  line
  line `(c) twenty-four part-time Members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall be a dentist of outstanding ability, proven administrative`
  line `capacity and integrity, possessing a postgraduate degree in dentistry from any University or`
  line `institutes of national importance and having experience of not less than twenty years in the`
  line `field of dentistry, out of which at least ten years shall be as a leader in the area of dental`
  line education.
  line
  line `(3) The following persons shall be the ex officio Members of the Commission,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the President of the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the President of the Dental Assessment and Rating Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the President of the Ethics and Dental Registration Board;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director General of Health Services, Directorate General of Health Services,`
  line `New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(e) Chief of the Centre for Dental Education and Research, All India Institute of`
  line `Medical Sciences, New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(f) Head of the Oral Health Sciences Centre, Postgraduate Institute of Medical`
  line `Education and Research, Chandigarh;`
  line
  line `(g) one person, not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India, to`
  line `represent the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, to be nominated by that Ministry;`
  line
  line `(h) the Chairperson, National Medical Commission or nominee from that`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(4) The following persons shall be appointed as part-time Members of the Commission,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) three Members, to be appointed from amongst persons of ability, integrity and`
  line `standing, who have special knowledge and professional experience in such areas`
  line `including management, law, medical ethics, health research, consumer or patient rights`
  line `advocacy, science and technology and economics, in such manner as may be prescribed,`
  line `for a term of four years;`
  line
  line `(b) ten Members to be appointed on rotational basis from amongst the nominees of`
  line `the States and Union territories under clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (2) of section 11`
  line `in the Dental Advisory Council, in such manner as may be prescribed, for a term of two`
  line years;
  line
  line `(c) nine members to be appointed on rotational basis from amongst the nominees of`
  line `the States and Union territories under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 11 in the`
  line `Dental Advisory Council, in such manner as may be prescribed, for a term of two years;`
  line
  line `(d) two dental faculties, from any Central or State or Autonomous Government`
  line `Institutes, doing exemplary work in the field of dental education, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government, in such manner as may be prescribed, for a term of four years.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (83655)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Search-cum-Selection Committee for appointment of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83655&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint.---`
  line
  line `(i) the Chairperson referred to in sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ii) part-time Members referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Secretary referred to in section 8; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the President and Members of Autonomous Boards referred to in section 16,`
  line
  line `on the recommendation of a Search-cum-Selection Committee consisting of---`
  line
  line `(a) the Cabinet Secretary---Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) three experts, possessing outstanding qualifications and experience of not less`
  line `than twenty-five years in the field of dental education, public health education and`
  line `health research, to be nominated by the Central Government, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed---Members;
  line
  line `(c) one person, possessing outstanding qualifications and experience of not less than`
  line `twenty-five years in the field of management or law or economics or science and`
  line `technology, to be nominated by the Central Government, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed---Member;
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India in charge of the Ministry of Health and`
  line `Family Welfare, to be the Convener---Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, within one month from the date of occurrence of any`
  line `vacancy, including by reason of death, resignation or removal, of the Chairperson or`
  line `Member or Secretary of the Commission or the President or Member of the Autonomous`
  line `Board, as the case may be, or within three months before the end of tenure of such person,`
  line `make a reference to the Search-cum-Selection Committee for filling up of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Search-cum-Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of at least three`
  line `names for every vacancy referred to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Search-cum-Selection Committee shall, before recommending any person for`
  line `appointment as the Chairperson or Member or Secretary, satisfy itself that such person does`
  line `not have any financial or other interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `such Chairperson or Member or Secretary.`
  line
  line `(5) No appointment of the Chairperson or Member or Secretary of the Commission or`
  line `the President or Member of the Autonomous Board, as the case may be, shall be invalid`
  line `merely by reason of any vacancy or absence of a Member in the Search-cum-Selection`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) to (5), the Search-cum-Selection`
  line `Committee may regulate its own procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (83656)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83656&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson appointed under sub-section (2) of section 4, and Member of the Commission`
  line `appointed or nominated under clauses (a) and (d) of sub-section (4) of section 4 shall not be`
  line `eligible for any extension of term beyond four years or for reappointment and such person`
  line `shall cease to hold office after attaining the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio Member shall continue as long as he holds the`
  line `office by virtue of which he is such Member.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a Member, other than an ex officio Member, is absent from three consecutive`
  line `ordinary meetings of the Commission and the cause of such absence is not attributable to`
  line `any valid reason in the opinion of the Commission, such Member shall be deemed to have`
  line `vacated the seat.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of,`
  line `the Chairperson and Members appointed or nominated under clauses (a) and (d) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4, other than an ex officio Member, shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson or a Member or Secretary of the Commission may,--`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing to the Central Government a notice of`
  line `not less than three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 7:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person may be relieved from duties earlier than three months or be`
  line `allowed to continue beyond three months until a successor is appointed, if the Central`
  line `Government so decides.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson and every Member of the Commission shall make declaration of his`
  line `assets and liabilities at the time of entering upon his office and at the time of demitting his`
  line `office and also declare his professional and commercial engagement or involvement in such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed, and such declaration shall be published on the`
  line `website of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson or a Member appointed or nominated under clauses (a) and (d) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4 or the Secretary, ceasing to hold office as such, shall not accept,`
  line `for a period of two years from the date of demitting such office, any employment, in any`
  line `capacity, including as a consultant or an expert, in any private dental institution, whose`
  line `matter has been dealt with by such person, directly or indirectly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein shall be construed as preventing such person from`
  line `accepting an employment in a body or institution, including dental institution, controlled or`
  line `maintained by the Central Government or a State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing herein shall prevent the Central Government from`
  line `permitting the Chairperson or Member or Secretary of the Commission to accept any`
  line `employment in any capacity, including as a consultant or expert in any private dental`
  line `institution whose matter has been dealt with by such Chairperson or Member or Secretary.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (83657)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal of Chairperson and Member of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83657&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by order, remove from office the Chairperson or any other Member,`
  line who---
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his`
  line `functions as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(f) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to`
  line `public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) No Member shall be removed under clauses (e) and (f) of sub-section (1) unless he`
  line `has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (83713)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment of Secretary, experts, professionals, officers and other employees of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83713&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Secretariat for the Commission to be headed by a`
  line `Secretary, to be appointed by the Central Government in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary of the Commission shall be a person of proven administrative capacity`
  line `and integrity, possessing such qualifications and experience as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary shall be appointed by the Central Government for a term of four years`
  line `and shall not be eligible for any extension or reappointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Secretary shall also be the Member Secretary of each of the Autonomous Boards`
  line `constituted under section 16.`
  line
  line `(5) The Secretary shall discharge such functions of the Commission, and of each of the`
  line `Autonomous Boards constituted under section 16, as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission may, for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act,`
  line `appoint such officers and other employees of the Commission, other than Secretary, as it`
  line `considers necessary, against the posts created by the Central Government on the`
  line `recommendation of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(7) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `the Secretary, officers and other employees of the Commission shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(8) The Commission may engage, in accordance with the procedure specified by`
  line `regulations, such number of experts, consultants and professionals of integrity and`
  line `outstanding ability, who have special knowledge and experience in such fields, including`
  line `dental education, public health, management, health economics, quality assurance, patient`
  line `advocacy, health research, science and technology, administration, finance, accounts and`
  line `law, as it deems necessary, to assist the Commission in the discharge of its functions under`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission may, to facilitate global mobility and employability of`
  line `registered professionals, invite such number of experts and domain specialists from a`
  line `foreign country, as it deems necessary, who have special knowledge of dental curriculum,`
  line `practical training and pattern of examination including licentiate examination of that`
  line `country, to the meetings of the Commission, in such manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (83659)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Meetings, etc., of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83659&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet at least once every`
  line `quarter at such time and place as may be appointed by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall preside at the meeting of the Commission and if, for any`
  line `reason, the Chairperson is unable to attend the meeting of the Commission, any other`
  line `Member, being the President of an Autonomous Board, nominated by the Chairperson, shall`
  line `preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the procedure to be followed at the meetings of the Commission is otherwise`
  line `provided by regulations, one-half of the total number of Members of the Commission`
  line `including the Chairperson shall constitute the quorum and all the acts of the Commission`
  line `shall be decided by a majority of the members present and voting and in the event of`
  line `equality of votes, the Chairperson, or in his absence, the President of the Autonomous Board`
  line `nominated under sub-section (2), shall have the casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) The general superintendence, direction and control of the administration of the`
  line `Commission shall vest in the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(5) No act done by the Commission shall be questioned on the ground of the existence of`
  line `a vacancy in, or a defect in the constitution of, the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (83660)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers and functions of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83660&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall, for ensuring`
  line `coordinated and integrated development of education and maintenance of the standards of`
  line `delivery of services, take all such steps, as it may think fit, and revise the same periodically,`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) lay down policies and regulate standards for the governance of dental education,`
  line `examination and training and make necessary regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) promote adoption of additional degrees or diplomas, higher qualifications,`
  line `including certification courses and development of soft skills for advancement of career`
  line `of the dentists and dental auxiliaries;`
  line
  line `(c) regulate dental institutions, dental researches, dentists and dental auxiliaries and`
  line `make necessary regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure that all admissions to undergraduate dental course, namely, Bachelor of`
  line `Dental Surgery in all dental institutions which are governed by the provisions of this Act`
  line `or any other law for the time being in force, shall be through National Eligibility-cumEntrance Test conducted under section 14 of the National Medical Commission`
  line `Act, 2019 (30 of 2019);`
  line
  line `(e) to identify and regulate any other category of dental auxiliaries;`
  line
  line `(f) to collaborate with industry and institutions for use of cutting-edge technology`
  line `and hybrid education to drive innovation and research in the field of dental education`
  line `and examinations and make necessary regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(g) assess the requirements in dental healthcare, including human resources for`
  line `dental health, career progression of dentists and dental auxiliaries and healthcare`
  line `infrastructure and develop a road map for meeting such requirements;`
  line
  line `(h) promote, coordinate and frame guidelines and lay down policies by making`
  line `necessary regulations for the proper functioning of the Commission, the Autonomous Boards, the Dental Advisory Council, the State Dental Councils and the Joint Dental`
  line Councils;
  line
  line `(i) ensure coordination among the Autonomous Boards;`
  line
  line `(j) take such measures, as may be necessary, to ensure compliance by the State`
  line `Dental Councils of the guidelines framed and regulations made under this Act for their`
  line `effective functioning under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) exercise appellate jurisdiction with respect to the decisions of the Autonomous`
  line Boards;
  line
  line `(l) promote preventive dental care services;`
  line
  line `(m) lay down policies and codes to ensure observance of professional ethics in dental`
  line `profession and to promote ethical conduct during the provision of care by dentists;`
  line
  line `(n) frame guidelines for determination of fees and all other charges in respect of fifty`
  line `per cent. of seats in private dental institutions and deemed to be Universities which are`
  line `governed under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) take measures to enhance skills and competency of registered professionals for`
  line `facilitating global mobility;`
  line
  line `(p) exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may delegate such of its functions (except the power to make`
  line `regulations) to the Autonomous Boards as it may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission may give such directions, as may deem necessary, to a State`
  line `Council for carrying out all or any of the provisions of this Act and the State Council shall`
  line `comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(5) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the signature of`
  line `the Secretary.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission may delegate such of its powers of administrative and financial`
  line `matters, as it deems fit, to the Secretary.`
  line
  line `(7) The Commission may constitute sub-committees and delegate such of its powers to`
  line `such sub-committees as may be necessary to enable them to accomplish specific tasks.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (83661)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Constitution and composition of Dental Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83661&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall constitute an advisory body to be known as the Dental Advisory Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall consist of a Chairperson and the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson of the Commission shall be the ex officio Chairperson of the`
  line Council;
  line
  line `(b) every ex officio member of the Commission appointed under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4, and the part-time members appointed under clauses (a) and (d) of sub-section`
  line `(4) of that section, shall be the ex officio members of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) one member to represent each State, who is the Dean or Principal of a`
  line `Government Dental College in that State, to be nominated by that State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term of office of the member shall continue as long as he holds the`
  line `post by virtue of which he has been nominated, subject to a maximum of four years;`
  line
  line `(d) one member to represent each Union territory, who is the Dean or Principal of a`
  line `Government Dental College in that Union territory, to be nominated by the Ministry of`
  line `Home Affairs in the Government of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term of office of the member shall continue as long as he holds the`
  line `post by virtue of which he has been nominated, subject to a maximum of four years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if there is no Government Dental College in any State or Union`
  line `territory, the State Government or in case of a Union territory, the Ministry of Home`
  line `Affairs shall nominate a member possessing such dental qualifications and experience,`
  line `as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(e) one member to represent each State and each Union territory from amongst the`
  line `members of the State Dental Council, to be nominated by that State Dental Council for a`
  line `term of four years and shall not be eligible for any extension or reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such member ceases to be a member of the State Dental Council`
  line `before the completion of his four year term, then, he shall cease to be a member of the`
  line `Dental Advisory Council as well, and in such an eventuality, the State Dental Council`
  line `shall nominate another member to represent that State or Union territory, as the case`
  line `may be, for the remaining term of office of the member in whose place he is so`
  line nominated;
  line
  line `(f) the Chairman, University Grants Commission;`
  line
  line `(g) the Director, National Assessment and Accreditation Council;`
  line
  line `(h) three members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst`
  line `persons holding the post of Director in the institutions of national importance or`
  line `Vice-Chancellor in the Universities;`
  line
  line `(i) Director General of Indian Council for Medical Research or his nominee not`
  line `below the rank of Scientist H;`
  line
  line `(j) Director General Dental Services, Army Dental Corps or nominee.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (83662)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of Dental Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83662&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall be the primary`
  line `platform through which the States and Union territories may put forth their views and`
  line `concerns before the Commission and help in shaping the overall agenda, policy and action`
  line `relating to dental education and training.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall advise the Commission on measures to determine and maintain,`
  line `and to coordinate maintenance of, the minimum standards in all matters relating to dental`
  line `education, training and research.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall advise the Commission on measures to enhance equitable access to`
  line `dental education and uniform system of examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (83663)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Meetings of Dental Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83663&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall meet at least once a`
  line `year at such time and place as may be decided by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall preside at the meeting of the Council and if for any reason the`
  line `Chairperson is unable to attend a meeting of the Council, such other member as nominated`
  line `by the Chairperson shall preside over the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the procedure is otherwise provided by regulations, fifty per cent. of the`
  line `members of the Council including the Chairperson shall form the quorum and all acts of the`
  line `Council shall be decided by a majority of the members present and voting.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (83664)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83664&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) All admissions to the undergraduate`
  line `course of Bachelor of Dental Surgery in all dental institutions which are governed by the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any other law for the time being in force shall be through National`
  line `Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test conducted under section 14 of the National Medical`
  line `Commission Act, 2019 (30 of 2019).`
  line
  line `(2) Till such time as the National Exit Test (Dental) becomes operational under`
  line `section 15, all admissions to the postgraduate courses of Master of Dental Surgery in all`
  line `dental institutions which are governed by the provisions of this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force shall be through National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test (MDS) to be`
  line `conducted by the designated authority appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall specify by regulations the manner of conducting common`
  line `counselling by the designated authority for admission to undergraduate and postgraduate`
  line `seats in all the dental institutions which are governed by the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the designated authority appointed or nominated by the Central`
  line `Government shall conduct the common counselling for all India seats and the designated`
  line `authority of the State Government shall conduct the common counselling for the seats at the`
  line `State level.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (83665)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `National Exit Test (Dental).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83665&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) A common final year undergraduate dental`
  line `examination, to be known as the ‘National Exit Test (Dental)’ shall be held for granting`
  line `licence to practice dentistry as dentists and for enrolment in the State Register or the`
  line `National Register, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall conduct the National Exit Test (Dental) through such`
  line `designated authority and in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Exit Test (Dental) shall become operational on such date, within three`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act, as may be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person with a foreign dental qualification shall have to qualify National Exit`
  line `Test (Dental) for the purpose of obtaining licence to practice dentistry as dentist and for enrolment in the State Register or the National Register, as the case may be, in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Exit Test (Dental) shall be the basis for admission to the postgraduate`
  line `dental education in dental institutions which are governed under the provisions of this Act or`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force and shall be done in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall specify by regulations the manner of conducting common`
  line `counselling by the designated authority for admission to the postgraduate seats in the dental`
  line `institutions referred to in sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) The designated authority of the Central Government shall conduct the common`
  line `counselling for All India seats and the designated authority of the State Government shall`
  line `conduct the common counselling for the seats at the State level.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (83666)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Constitution of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83666&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, constitute the following Autonomous Boards, under the overall supervision of`
  line `the Commission, to perform the functions assigned to such Boards under this Act,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the Dental Assessment and Rating Board; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Ethics and Dental Registration Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Autonomous Board shall carry out its functions under this Act in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (83667)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Composition of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83667&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Autonomous Board shall consist`
  line `of a President, not more than two whole-time Members and not more than two part-time`
  line Members.
  line
  line `(2) The President of each Autonomous Board, two whole-time Members and one parttime Member of the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board, and one`
  line `whole-time Member and one part-time Member of the Dental Assessment and Rating Board`
  line `and of the Ethics and Dental Registration Board, shall be persons of outstanding ability,`
  line `proven administrative capacity and integrity, possessing a postgraduate degree in any`
  line `discipline of dentistry from any University and having hands-on clinical experience of not`
  line `less than fifteen years, out of which at least seven years shall be as a leader in the area of`
  line `dental education.`
  line
  line `(3) The second whole-time Member of the Dental Assessment and Rating Board shall be`
  line `a person of outstanding ability and integrity, possessing a postgraduate degree in any of the`
  line `disciplines of management, quality assurance, law or science and technology from any`
  line `University, having experience of not less than fifteen years in such field, out of which at`
  line `least seven years shall be as a leader.`
  line
  line `(4) The second whole-time Member of the Ethics and Dental Registration Board shall be`
  line `a person of outstanding ability who has demonstrated public record of work on dental or medical ethics or a person of outstanding ability possessing a postgraduate degree in any of`
  line `the disciplines of quality assurance, public health, law or patient advocacy from any`
  line `University and having experience of not less than fifteen years in such field, out of which at`
  line `least seven years shall be as a leader.`
  line
  line `(5) The second part-time Member of the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental`
  line `Education Board, the Dental Assessment and Rating Board and the Ethics and Dental`
  line `Registration Board shall be chosen from amongst the Members appointed under clause (c)`
  line `of sub-section (4) of section 4 in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (83668)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Search-cum-Selection Committee for appointment of President and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83668&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall appoint the President and Members of the`
  line `Autonomous Boards, except Members referred to in sub-section (5) of section 17, on the`
  line `recommendations made by the Search-cum-Selection Committee constituted under section 5`
  line `in accordance with the procedure specified in that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (83669)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of President and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83669&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `President and Members (other than part-time Members) of each Autonomous Board shall`
  line `hold the office for a term not exceeding four years and shall not be eligible for any extension`
  line `or reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that part-time Members of each Autonomous Board shall hold the office for a`
  line `term of two years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the President or a Member shall cease to hold office after attaining`
  line `the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `the President and Members (other than part-time Members) of an Autonomous Board shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that part-time Members of each Autonomous Board shall be entitled for such`
  line `allowances as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (3), (5), (6) and (7) of section 6 relating to other terms`
  line `and conditions of service of, and section 7 relating to removal from the office of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members of the Commission shall also be applicable to the President and`
  line `Members of the Autonomous Boards.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (83670)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Advisory committees of experts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83670&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Autonomous Board, except the Ethics`
  line `and Dental Registration Board, shall be assisted by such advisory committees of experts as`
  line `may be constituted by the Commission for the efficient discharge of the functions of such`
  line `Boards under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the advisory committee for the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental`
  line `Education Board shall also have at least one member from amongst personnel of each`
  line `category of the dental auxiliaries to be nominated by the Chairperson of the Commission, in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ethics and Dental Registration Board shall be assisted by such ethics committees`
  line `of experts as may be constituted by the Commission for the efficient discharge of the`
  line `functions of that Board under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (83671)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Staff of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83671&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The experts, consultants, professionals, officers and`
  line `other employees appointed under section 8 shall be made available to the Autonomous`
  line `Boards in such number, and in such manner, as may be specified by regulations by the`
  line `Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the experts and domain specialists from foreign countries invited by the`
  line `Commission under sub-section (8) of section 8 shall also be made available to the`
  line `Autonomous Boards in such number and manner, as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (83672)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Meetings, etc., of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83672&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Autonomous Board shall meet`
  line `at least once every month, or earlier, as the case may be, at such time and place as it may`
  line appoint.
  line
  line `(2) All decisions of the Autonomous Boards shall be made by majority of votes of the`
  line `President and Members.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 28, a person who is aggrieved by any decision of`
  line `an Autonomous Board may prefer an appeal to the Commission against such decision within`
  line `thirty days of the communication of such decision; and the Commission shall, after giving`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal within a period of sixty days from the`
  line `date of such appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President of the concerned Board shall not attend proceedings of the`
  line `hearing of the appeal made against the decision of his Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (83674)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Powers of Autonomous Boards and delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83674&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of`
  line `each Autonomous Board shall have such administrative and financial powers as may be`
  line `delegated to it by the Commission to enable such Board to function efficiently.`
  line
  line `(2) The President of an Autonomous Board may further delegate any of his powers to a`
  line `Member or an officer of that Board, and such person shall exercise his powers subject to the`
  line `general control, supervision and direction of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (83675)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers and functions of Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83675&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board shall perform`
  line `the following functions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) determine minimum requirements and standards of dental education at`
  line `undergraduate level and postgraduate level for dentists and dental auxiliaries in`
  line `accordance with the regulations made under this Act, and oversee all aspects relating`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(b) develop competency based dynamic curriculum at undergraduate level and`
  line `postgraduate level for dentists and dental auxiliaries for addressing the needs of basic`
  line `dental care services, including public dentistry and community dental care, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of regulations made under this Act with a view to`
  line `develop appropriate skill, knowledge, attitude, values and ethics to provide dental care,`
  line `impart dental education and conduct dental research;`
  line
  line `(c) frame guidelines for setting up of dental institutions for imparting undergraduate`
  line `courses and postgraduate courses for dentists and dental auxiliaries, having regard to the`
  line `needs of the country and the global norms, in accordance with the regulations made`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) determine the minimum requirements and standards for conducting courses and`
  line `examinations at undergraduate level and postgraduate level for dentists and dental`
  line `auxiliaries in dental institutions, having regard to the needs of creativity at local levels,`
  line `including designing of some courses by individual institutions, in accordance with`
  line `provisions of the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) determine standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education`
  line `in dental institutions providing undergraduate and postgraduate dental education for`
  line `dentists and dental auxiliaries in accordance with provisions of the regulations made`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) facilitate development and training of faculty members teaching undergraduate`
  line `courses for dentists and dental auxiliaries;`
  line
  line `(g) facilitate research and the international student and faculty exchange programme`
  line `relating to undergraduate and postgraduate dental education;`
  line
  line `(h) specify norms for compulsory annual disclosures, electronically or otherwise, by`
  line `dental institutions, in respect of their functions which have a bearing on the interest of`
  line `all stakeholders, including students, faculty, State Dental Councils, Joint Dental Council,`
  line `the Commission and the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) grant recognition to a dental qualification at the undergraduate level and`
  line `postgraduate level for dentists and dental auxiliaries.`
  line
  line `(2) The Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board shall, in the`
  line `discharge of its duties, make such recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the`
  line `Commission, as it deems necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (83676)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers and functions of Dental Assessment and Rating Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83676&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Dental`
  line `Assessment and Rating Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) determine the procedure for assessing and rating the dental institutions for their`
  line `compliance with the standards laid down by the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate`
  line `Dental Education Board in accordance with the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) grant permission for establishment of a new dental institution, or to start any`
  line `postgraduate course or to increase number of seats, in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 28;`
  line
  line `(c) conduct inspections of dental institutions using Information Technology based`
  line `tools or otherwise for assessing and rating such institutions in accordance with the`
  line `regulations made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Dental Assessment and Rating Board may, if it deems necessary,`
  line `hire and authorise any other third party agency or accreditation body or persons for`
  line `carrying out inspections of dental institutions for assessing and rating such institutions:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where inspection of dental institutions is carried out by such`
  line `third party agency or accreditation body or persons authorised by the Dental Assessment`
  line `and Rating Board, it shall be obligatory on such institutions to provide access to such`
  line `agency or person;`
  line
  line `(d) conduct, or where it deems necessary, empanel independent rating agencies to`
  line `conduct, inspection to assess and rate all dental institutions, within such period of their`
  line `opening, and every year thereafter, at such time, and in such manner, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Dental Assessment and Rating Board may conduct evaluation and`
  line `assessment of any dental institution at any time, either directly or through any other`
  line `expert having integrity and experience of dental profession and without any prior notice`
  line `and assess and evaluate the performance, standards and benchmarks of such dental`
  line institution;
  line
  line `(e) make available on its website or in public domain the assessment and ratings of`
  line `dental institutions at regular intervals in accordance with the regulations made under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(f) take such measures, including issuing warning, imposition of monetary penalty,`
  line `reducing intake or stoppage of admissions and recommending to the Commission for`
  line `withdrawal of recognition, against a dental institution for failure to maintain the`
  line `minimum essential standards specified by the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental`
  line `Education Board, in accordance with the regulations made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the monetary penalty so imposed shall not be less than one-tenth, and`
  line `not more than five times, of the total amount charged, by whatever name called, by such`
  line `institution for one full batch of students of undergraduate course or postgraduate course,`
  line `as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Dental Assessment and Rating Board shall consult the`
  line `Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board before recommending to the`
  line `Commission for withdrawal of recognition of a dental institution that fails to maintain`
  line `the minimum essential standards specified by the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate`
  line `Dental Education Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Dental Assessment and Rating Board shall, in the discharge of its functions,`
  line `make such recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the Commission, as it deems`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (83677)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Powers and functions of Ethics and Dental Registration Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83677&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ethics`
  line `and Dental Registration Board shall perform the following functions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) maintain an online and live National Registers of all licensed dentists and dental`
  line `auxiliaries in accordance with the provisions of section 30;`
  line
  line `(b) regulate the standards, scope of practice, professional conduct and promote`
  line `dental ethics in accordance with the regulations made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Ethics and Dental Registration Board shall ensure compliance of`
  line `the code of professional and ethical conduct through the State Dental Council in a case`
  line `where such State Dental Council has been conferred power to take disciplinary actions`
  line `in respect of professional or ethical misconduct by dentists under respective State Acts;`
  line
  line `(c) approve or reject the application for registration or suspend or cancel registration`
  line `or licence granted to dentists and dental auxiliaries on grounds of professional and`
  line `ethical misconduct;`
  line
  line `(d) develop mechanisms to have continuous interaction with State Dental Councils to`
  line `effectively promote and regulate the conduct of dentists and professionals;`
  line
  line `(e) exercise appellate jurisdiction under sub-section (5) of section 29 with respect to`
  line `the actions taken by a State Dental Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ethics and Dental Registration Board shall, in the discharge of its duties, make`
  line `such recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the Commission, as it deems`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (83714)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Permission for establishment of new dental college or to start postgraduate course or to increase number of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83714&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall establish a new dental college`
  line `or start any postgraduate course or increase number of seats without obtaining prior`
  line `permission of the Dental Assessment and Rating Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Dental Assessment and Rating Board shall consult the Under-Graduate`
  line `and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board before approving or disapproving such`
  line permission.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of obtaining permission under sub-section (1), a person may submit`
  line `a scheme to the Dental Assessment and Rating Board in such form, containing such`
  line `particulars, accompanied by such fee, and in such manner, as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(3) The Dental Assessment and Rating Board shall, having due regard to the criteria`
  line `specified in section 28, consider the scheme received under sub-section (2) and either`
  line `approve or disapprove such scheme within a period of six months from the date of such`
  line `receipt:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Dental Assessment and Rating Board shall consult the Under-Graduate`
  line `and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board before approving such scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before disapproving the scheme, an opportunity to rectify the`
  line `defects, if any, shall be given to the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a scheme is approved under sub-section (3), such approval shall be the`
  line `permission under sub-section (1) to establish new dental college or to start any postgraduate`
  line `course or to increase number of seats, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a scheme is disapproved under sub-section (3), or where no decision is taken`
  line `within six months of submitting a scheme under sub-section (1), the person concerned may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Commission for approval of the scheme within fifteen days of such`
  line `disapproval or, as the case may be, lapse of six months, in such manner as may be specified`
  line `by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall decide the appeal received under sub-section (5) within a`
  line `period of sixty days from the date of receipt of the appeal and in case the Commission`
  line `approves the scheme, such approval shall be the permission under sub-section (1) to`
  line `establish a new dental college or to start any postgraduate course or to increase number of`
  line `seats, as the case may be, and in case the Commission disapproves the Scheme, or fails to`
  line `give its decision within the specified period, the person concerned may prefer a second`
  line `appeal to the Central Government within thirty days of communication of such disapproval`
  line `or, as the case may be, lapse of specified period.`
  line
  line `(7) The Dental Assessment and Rating Board may conduct evaluation and assessment of`
  line `any dental institution at any time, either directly or through any other expert having integrity`
  line `and experience in dental profession, without any prior notice and assess and evaluate the`
  line `performance, standards and benchmarks of such dental institution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the term "person" includes a University,`
  line `trust or any other association of persons or body of individuals, but does not include the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (83679)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Criteria for approving or disapproving scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83679&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `While approving or`
  line `disapproving a scheme under section 27, the Dental Assessment and Rating Board, or the`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, shall take into consideration the following criteria,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) adequacy of financial resources;`
  line
  line `(b) whether adequate academic faculty and other necessary facilities have been`
  line `provided to ensure proper functioning of dental college or undertaken to be provided`
  line `within the time-limit specified in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) whether adequate hospital facilities have been provided or undertaken to be`
  line `provided within the time-limit specified in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(d) such other factors as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (83680)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `State Dental Council or Joint Dental Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83680&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall,`
  line `within one year of the commencement of this Act, take necessary steps to establish a State`
  line `Dental Council having the following composition, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a dentist of outstanding ability, proven administrative capacity and integrity and`
  line `possessing a postgraduate degree in any discipline of dentistry from any University or`
  line `institute of national importance with experience of not less than twenty years in the field`
  line `of dentistry, out of which at least ten years shall be as a leader, to be appointed by the`
  line `State Government---Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) one representative of the department of medical education or health services in`
  line `the State Government not below the rank of Additional Director--- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) four persons to be elected by dentists registered in the State Register from among`
  line `themselves, in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government--- Members;`
  line
  line `(d) two persons, having experience of not less than ten years in any field of dentistry`
  line `from any Government Dental College in that State, to be nominated by the State`
  line `Government---Members:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the State does not have a Government Dental College, the State`
  line `Government may nominate one of the senior-most dentist with minimum of ten years'`
  line `service in any Government hospital or in the dental department of a Government`
  line `Medical College;`
  line
  line `(e) two persons having experience of not less than ten years in any field of dentistry`
  line `from any recognised private dental college in the State, to be nominated by the State`
  line `Government--Members:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the State does not have a private dental college, the State`
  line `Government may nominate one of the senior-most dentist with minimum of ten years'`
  line `service in any private hospital or in the dental department of a private medical college;`
  line
  line `(f) two persons of eminence having experience of not less than ten years in any field`
  line `of dentistry, to be nominated by the State Government--Members.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Dental Council shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having`
  line `perpetual succession and a common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall by the same name sue or`
  line `be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the State Dental Council and Members elected or nominated`
  line `under clauses (c), (d), (e) and (f) of sub-section (1) shall hold office for a term not exceeding`
  line `four years from the date on which they enter upon their office and shall not be eligible for`
  line `extension or reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall cease to hold office after attaining the age of seventy`
  line years.
  line
  line `(4) Where a State Act confers power upon the State Dental Council to take disciplinary`
  line `actions in respect of any professional or ethical misconduct by a registered dentist or`
  line `professional, the State Dental Council shall act in accordance with the regulations made, and`
  line `the guidelines framed, under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time as a State Dental Council is established in a State, the Ethics`
  line `and Dental Registration Board shall receive the complaints and grievances relating to any`
  line `professional or ethical misconduct against a registered dentist or professional in that State in`
  line `accordance with such procedure as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Ethics and Dental Registration Board or the State Dental`
  line `Council, as the case may be, shall give an opportunity of being heard to the dentist or`
  line `professional concerned before taking any action, including imposition of any monetary`
  line `penalty against such person.`
  line
  line `(5) A registered professional or any other person who is aggrieved by any action taken`
  line `by a State Dental Council under sub-section (4) may prefer an appeal to the Ethics and`
  line `Dental Registration Board within sixty days against such action, and the Ethics and Dental`
  line `Registration Board shall decide on the appeal within a period of sixty days and the decision,`
  line `if any, of the Ethics and Dental Registration Board thereupon shall be binding on the State`
  line `Dental Council, unless a second appeal is preferred under sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `(6) A registered professional or any other person who is aggrieved by the decision of the`
  line `Ethics and Dental Registration Board may prefer an appeal to the Commission within sixty`
  line `days of communication of such decision and the Commission shall dispose of such appeal`
  line `within a period of ninety days from the date of that appeal.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this section, two or more States`
  line `Governments may enter into an agreement to constitute a Joint Dental Council with representation of the participating States, not exceeding the composition specified in subsection (1), to be in force for such period and subject to renewal for such further period, as`
  line `may be specified in the agreement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) "State" includes Union territory and the expressions "State Government" and`
  line `"State Dental Council", in relation to a Union territory, shall respectively mean the`
  line `"Central Government" and "Union Territory Dental Council";`
  line
  line `(b) the expression professional or ethical misconduct includes any act of`
  line `commission or omission as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (83681)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `National Register and State Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83681&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ethics and Dental Registration`
  line `Board shall maintain an online and live National Register for Dentists containing the name,`
  line `address, all recognised qualifications possessed by a licensed dentist and such other`
  line `particulars as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ethics and Dental Registration Board shall also maintain a separate online and`
  line `live National Register for each category of dental auxiliaries, containing the name, address,`
  line `recognised qualifications possessed by the dental auxiliaries and such other particulars as`
  line `may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Register referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be maintained in`
  line `such form, including in electronic or digital form and in such manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(4) The manner in which a name or qualification may be added to, or removed from, the`
  line `National Register and the grounds for removal thereof, shall be such as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(5) The National Register shall be a public document within the meaning of section 74`
  line `of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(6) The National Register shall be made available to the public in form of a digital portal`
  line `accessible on the website of the Ethics and Dental Registration Board in such manner and`
  line `form as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) Every State Dental Council shall maintain and regularly update the State Register for`
  line `Dentists and the State Register for dental auxiliaries in the specified electronic format and`
  line `supply a physical copy of the same to the Ethics and Dental Registration Board within three`
  line `months of the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) The Ethics and Dental Registration Board shall ensure electronic synchronisation of`
  line `the National Register and the State Registers in such manner that any change in one register`
  line `is automatically reflected in the other register.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (83715)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Rights of persons to have licence to practice and to be enrolled in National Register or State Register and their obligations thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83715&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who qualifies`
  line `the National Exit Test (Dental) held under section 15 shall be granted a licence to practice dentistry and shall have his name and qualifications enrolled in the National Register or a`
  line `State Register, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has been registered in the Indian Dental Register maintained`
  line `under the Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948) prior to the coming into force of this Act and`
  line `before the National Exit Test (Dental) becomes operational under sub-section (3) of section`
  line `15, shall be deemed to have been registered under this Act and be enrolled in the National`
  line `Register maintained under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No person who has obtained dental qualification from a dental institution established`
  line `in any country outside India and is recognised as a dentist in that country, shall, after the`
  line `commencement of this Act and the National Exit Test (Dental) becomes operational under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 15, be enrolled in the National Register unless he qualifies the`
  line `National Exit Test (Dental).`
  line
  line `(3) When a person whose name is entered in the State Register or the National Register,`
  line `as the case may be, obtains any title, diploma or other qualification for proficiency in`
  line `sciences or public health or dentistry which is a recognised dental qualification under`
  line `section 33 or section 34 or section 35, as the case may be, he shall be entitled to have such`
  line `title, diploma or qualification entered against his name in the State Register or the National`
  line `Register, as the case may be, in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (83683)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Bar to practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83683&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than a person who is enrolled in the State`
  line `Register or the National Register, as the case may be, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be allowed to practice dentistry as a qualified dentist;`
  line
  line `(b) hold office as a dentist or any other office, by whatever name called, which is`
  line `meant to be held by a dentist;`
  line
  line `(c) be entitled to sign or authenticate a medical or fitness certificate or any other`
  line `certificate relating to dentistry, required by any law to be signed or authenticated by a`
  line `duly qualified dentist;`
  line
  line `(d) be entitled to give evidence at any inquest or in any court of law as an expert`
  line `under section 45 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) on any matter relating to`
  line `dentistry:`
  line
  line `Provided that a foreign citizen who is enrolled in his country as a dentist in accordance`
  line `with the law regulating the registration of dentists in that country may be permitted`
  line `temporary registration in India for such period and in such manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes any of the provisions of this section shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend`
  line `to five lakh rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (83684)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Recognition of dental qualifications granted by Universities or dental institutions in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83684&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The dental qualification granted by any University or dental`
  line `institution in India shall be listed and maintained by the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board in such manner as may be specified by regulations and such dental`
  line `qualification shall be a recognised dental qualification for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any University or dental institution in India which grants an undergraduate or`
  line `postgraduate dental qualification not included in the list maintained by the Under-Graduate`
  line `and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board shall apply to that Board for granting`
  line `recognition to such qualification.`
  line
  line `(3) The Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board shall examine the`
  line `application for grant of recognition to a dental qualification within a period of six months in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board decides to`
  line `grant recognition to a dental qualification, it shall include such dental qualification in the list`
  line `maintained by it and also specify the date of effect of such recognition.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board decides not`
  line `to grant recognition to a dental qualification, the University or the dental institution`
  line `concerned may prefer an appeal to the Commission for grant of recognition within sixty`
  line `days of the communication of such decision, in such manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall examine the appeal received under sub-section (5) within`
  line `sixty days from the date of filing of appeal and after giving an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such orders, as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the Commission decides not to grant recognition to the dental qualification or`
  line `fails to take a decision within the specified period, the University or the dental institution`
  line `concerned may prefer a second appeal to the Central Government within thirty days of the`
  line `communication of such decision or lapse of the specified period, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(8) All dental qualifications which have been recognised before the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act and are included in Part I and Part II of the Schedule to the`
  line `Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948), shall also be recognised dental qualifications for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, and shall be listed and maintained by the Under-Graduate and`
  line `Post-Graduate Dental Education Board in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (83685)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Recognition of dental qualifications granted by dental institutions outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83685&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any primary dental qualification or higher dental qualification which is`
  line `recognised for enrolment as a dentist in a foreign country shall, in respect of a person who`
  line `qualifies the National Exit Test (Dental) for primary dental qualification, or the Screening`
  line `Test for higher dental qualification, be deemed to be a recognised dental qualification for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), conduct Screening Test`
  line `for higher dental qualification through such designated authority, and in such manner, as`
  line `may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) All dental qualifications which have been recognised before the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act and are included in Part III of the Schedule to the Dentists Act,`
  line `1948 (16 of 1948), shall also be recognised dental qualifications for the purposes of this Act, and shall be listed and maintained by the Commission in such manner as may be specified`
  line `by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (83686)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Recognition of dental qualifications granted by statutory or other body in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83686&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The dental qualifications granted by any statutory or other dental body in India`
  line `which are covered by the categories listed in the Schedule shall be recognised dental`
  line `qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Commission, and`
  line `having regard to the objects of this Act, by notification, add to, or, as the case may be, omit`
  line `from, the Schedule any categories of dental qualifications granted by a statutory or other`
  line `body in India and on such addition, or as the case may be, omission, the dental qualifications`
  line `granted by such statutory or other body in India shall be, or shall cease to be, recognised`
  line `dental qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (83717)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Withdrawal of recognition granted to dental qualification granted by dental institutions in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83717&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, upon receiving the recommendation from the Dental`
  line `Assessment and Rating Board under section 25, or otherwise, if the Commission is of the`
  line `opinion that--`
  line
  line `(a) the courses of study and examination to be undergone in, or the proficiency`
  line `required from candidates at any examination held by, a University or dental institution`
  line `do not conform to the standards specified by the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate`
  line `Dental Education Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) the standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education in`
  line `dental institution as determined by the Under-Graduate and Post-Graduate Dental`
  line `Education Board are not adhered to by any University or dental institution, and such`
  line `University or dental institution has failed to take necessary corrective action to maintain`
  line `specified minimum standards,`
  line
  line `the Commission may initiate action in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission shall, before taking any action for suo motu withdrawal of`
  line `recognition granted to the dental qualification awarded by a University or dental institution,`
  line `impose penalty in accordance with the provisions of clause (f) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 25.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, after making such further inquiry as it deems fit, and after`
  line `holding consultations with the concerned State Government and the authority of the`
  line `concerned University or dental institution, comes to the conclusion that the recognition`
  line `granted to a dental qualification ought to be withdrawn, it may, by order, withdraw`
  line `recognition granted to such dental qualification and direct the Under-Graduate and PostGraduate Dental Education Board to amend the entries against the University or dental`
  line `institution concerned in the list maintained by that Board to the effect that the recognition`
  line `granted to such dental qualification is withdrawn with effect from the date specified in that`
  line order.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (83688)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `De-recognition of dental qualifications granted by dental institutions outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83688&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Where, after verification with the authority in any country outside India, the`
  line `Commission is of the opinion that a recognised dental qualification granted by dental`
  line `institutions outside India which is included in the list maintained by it is to be de-recognised, it may, by order, de-recognise such dental qualification and remove it from the`
  line `list maintained by the Commission with effect from the date of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (83689)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83689&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Commission grants of`
  line `such sums of money as the Central Government may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (83690)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `National Dental Commission Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83690&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a fund to be`
  line `called ---the National Dental Commission Fund which shall form part of the public account`
  line `of India and there shall be credited thereto---`
  line
  line `(a) all fees, penalties and charges received by the Commission and the Autonomous`
  line Boards;
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Commission from such other sources as may be decided`
  line `by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for making payment towards---`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson, Members appointed or`
  line `nominated under clauses (a) and (d) of sub-section (4) of section 4 and the Secretary of`
  line `the Commission, the Presidents and Members of the Autonomous Boards and the`
  line `administrative expenses including the salaries and allowances payable to the officers and`
  line `other employees of the Commission and Autonomous Boards;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses incurred in carrying out the provisions of this Act, including in`
  line `connection with the discharge of the functions of the Commission and the Autonomous`
  line Boards.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (83691)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Audit and accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83691&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and`
  line `other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred`
  line `in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other persons appointed by`
  line `him in connection with the audit of the accounts of the Commission shall have the same`
  line `rights and privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General generally has in connection with the audit of Government accounts and in`
  line `particular, shall have the right to demand the production of, and complete access to, records,`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the`
  line `office of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission as certified by the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral of India or any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit`
  line `report thereon, shall be forwarded annually by the Commission to the Central Government which shall cause the same to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (83692)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Furnishing of returns and reports to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83692&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commission shall furnish to the Central Government, at such time, in such form and in such`
  line `manner, as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such reports and`
  line `statements, containing such particulars in regard to any matter under the jurisdiction of the`
  line `Commission, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall prepare, once every year, in such form and at such time as`
  line `may be prescribed, an annual report, giving a summary of its activities during the previous`
  line `year and copies of the report shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid by the Central`
  line `Government, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (83694)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to Commission and Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83694&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Commission and the Autonomous Boards shall, in exercise of their powers and discharge of`
  line `their functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the`
  line `Central Government may give in writing to them from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission and the Autonomous Boards shall, as far as practicable,`
  line `be given an opportunity to express their views before any direction is given under this`
  line sub-section.
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government as to whether a question is one of policy or`
  line `not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (83695)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83695&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Central Government may give such directions on questions of policy, as it may deem`
  line `necessary, to a State Government for carrying out all or any of the provisions of this Act and`
  line `the State Government shall comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government as to whether a question is one of policy or`
  line `not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (83696)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Information to be furnished by Commission and publication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83696&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commission shall furnish such reports, copies of its minutes, abstracts of its accounts, and`
  line `other information to the Central Government as that Government may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may publish, in such manner as it may think fit, the reports,`
  line `minutes, abstracts of accounts and other information furnished to it under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (83697)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Obligation of Universities and dental institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83697&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Every University and dental`
  line `institution governed under this Act shall maintain a website at all times and display on its`
  line `website all such information as may be required by the Commission or an Autonomous`
  line `Board, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (83698)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Completion of courses of studies in dental institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83698&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, any student who was studying for a degree, diploma or certificate in any dental institution immediately before the commencement of this Act shall`
  line `continue to so study and complete his course for such degree, diploma or certificate, and`
  line `such institution shall continue to provide instructions and examination for such student in`
  line `accordance with the syllabus and studies as existed before such commencement, and such`
  line `student shall be deemed to have completed his course of study under this Act and shall be`
  line `awarded degree, diploma or certificate under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where recognition granted to a`
  line `dental institution has lapsed, whether by efflux of time or by its voluntary surrender or for`
  line `any other reason whatsoever, such dental institution shall continue to maintain and provide`
  line `the minimum standards required to be provided under this Act till such time as all`
  line `candidates who are admitted in that dental institution complete their study.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (83699)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Joint sittings of Commission with relevant regulatory bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83699&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Commission`
  line `shall, at least once a year, hold a meeting with the National Medical Commission, the`
  line `Pharmacy Council of India, the Indian Nursing Council, National Commission for Indian`
  line `System of Medicine, the National Commission for Homoeopathy and the National`
  line `Commission for Allied and Healthcare Professions or the corresponding National Regulator`
  line `for regulating the above professions, at such time and place as they mutually appoint, to`
  line `enhance the interface between different workforce categories in modern system of medicine,`
  line `develop consensus on issues and promote team based approach to healthcare delivery.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (83700)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `State Government to promote preventive and promotive dental care in rural areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83700&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government may, for the purposes of addressing or promoting public`
  line `dentistry and community dental care in rural areas, take necessary measures to enhance the`
  line `capacity of the dental professionals.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (83712)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Chairperson, Members, officers of Commission and of Autonomous Boards to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83712&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the`
  line `Commission and the President, Members and officers and other employees of the`
  line `Autonomous Boards shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (83702)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83702&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal`
  line `proceeding shall lie against the Government, the Commission or any Autonomous Board or`
  line `a State Dental Council or any Committee thereof, or any officer or other employee of the`
  line `Government or of the Commission acting under this Act for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (83703)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83703&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable`
  line `under this Act except upon a complaint in writing made in this behalf by an officer`
  line `authorised by the Commission or the Ethics and Dental Registration Board or a State Dental`
  line `Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (83704)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83704&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, the`
  line `Central Government is of opinion that---`
  line
  line `(a) the Commission is unable to discharge the functions and duties imposed on it by`
  line `or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Commission has persistently made default in complying with any direction`
  line `issued by the Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, supersede the Commission for such period,`
  line `not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section, the Central`
  line `Government shall give a reasonable opportunity to the Commission to show cause as to why`
  line `it should not be superseded and shall consider the explanations and objections, if any, of the`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the`
  line Commission,--
  line
  line `(a) all the Members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as`
  line such;
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this`
  line `Act, be exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Commission, shall, until the`
  line `Commission is re-constituted under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such`
  line `person or persons as the Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Commission shall, until the Commission`
  line `is re-constituted under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued`
  line `under sub-section (1), the Central Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further term not exceeding six months,`
  line `as it may consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) re-constitute the Commission by fresh appointment and in such case the`
  line `Members who vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be`
  line `deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time before the expiration of the`
  line `period of supersession, whether as originally specified under sub-section (1) or as`
  line `extended under this sub-section, take action under clause (b) of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1)`
  line `and a full report of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to`
  line `such action to be laid before both Houses of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (83705)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83705&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such`
  line `rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointing ten Members of the Commission on rotational basis`
  line `from amongst the nominees of the States and Union territories in the Dental Advisory`
  line `Council under clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of appointing nine members of the Commission under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of nominating two members from amongst dental faculties, under`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the Chairperson and Members under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and the manner of making declaration under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications and experience to be possessed by the Secretary of the`
  line `Commission under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(g) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the Secretary, officers and other employees of the Commission under sub-section (7)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(h) the other powers and functions of the Commission under clause (p) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(i) the dental qualifications and experience to be possessed by a member under the`
  line `second proviso to clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of choosing second part-time Members under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(k) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the President and Members of an Autonomous Board and the allowances payable to`
  line `part-time Members under sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line `(l) the form for preparing annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 40;`
  line
  line `(m) the time within which, and the form and the manner in which, the reports and`
  line `statements shall be furnished by the Commission under sub-section (1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(n) the form and the time for preparing annual report under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 41;`
  line
  line `(o) the amount of compensation payable to employees under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 58;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (83706)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83706&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may, after previous publication,`
  line `by notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such`
  line `regulations may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the functions to be discharged by the Secretary of the Commission under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure in accordance with which experts, consultants and`
  line `professionals may be engaged, or the experts and domain specialists from foreign`
  line `country may be invited, and the number of such experts and professionals under`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed at the meetings of the Commission under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the quality and standards to be maintained in dental education under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of regulating dental institutions, dental research, dentists and`
  line `dental auxiliaries under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of functioning of the Commission, the Autonomous Boards, the`
  line `State Dental Councils and the Joint Dental Councils under clause (h) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure to be followed at the meetings of the Dental Advisory Council`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of conducting common counselling by the designated authority`
  line `for admission to the undergraduate and postgraduate dental education under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(i) the designated authority, and the manner for conducting the National Exit Test`
  line `(Dental) under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which a person with foreign dental qualification shall qualify`
  line `National Exit Test (Dental) and the manner of his enrolment in the State Register or`
  line `the National Register under sub-section (4) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which admission to the postgraduate dental education shall be`
  line `made on the basis of National Exit Test (Dental) under sub-section (5) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of conducting common counselling by the designated authority for`
  line `admission to the postgraduate dental education under sub-section (6) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of nominating one member from amongst personnel of each`
  line `category of the dental auxiliaries to the advisory committee for the Under-Graduate`
  line `and Post-Graduate Dental Education Board under the proviso to sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(n) the number of, and the manner in which, the experts, professionals, officers`
  line `and other employees, including the experts and domain specialists from foreign`
  line `countries invited by the Commission, under sub-section (8) of section 8 shall be`
  line `made available by the Commission to the Autonomous Boards under section 21;`
  line
  line `(o) the competency based dynamic curriculum at undergraduate level and`
  line `postgraduate level under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of imparting undergraduate courses and postgraduate courses for`
  line `dentists and dental auxiliaries by dental institutions under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(q) the minimum requirements and standards for conducting courses and`
  line `examinations at undergraduate level and postgraduate level for dentists and dental`
  line `auxiliaries in dental institutions under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(r) the standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education at`
  line `undergraduate level and postgraduate level for dentists and dental auxiliaries in`
  line `dental institutions under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(s) the procedure for assessing and rating of dental institutions under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(t) the manner of carrying out inspections of dental institutions for assessing and`
  line `rating such institutions under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner of conducting, and the manner of empaneling independent rating`
  line `agencies to conduct assessment and rating of dental institutions and the time period`
  line `for such assessment and rating under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of making available on website or in public domain the`
  line `assessment and ratings of dental institutions under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 25;`
  line
  line `(w) the measures to be taken against a dental institution for failure to maintain`
  line `the minimum essential standards under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of regulating professional conduct and promoting dental ethics`
  line `under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(y) the form of scheme, the particulars thereof, the fee to be accompanied and the`
  line `manner of submitting scheme for establishing new dental college or for starting any`
  line `postgraduate course or for increasing number of seats under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(z) the manner of preferring an appeal to the Commission for approval of the`
  line `scheme under sub-section (5) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(za) the other factors under clause (d) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(zb) the manner of taking disciplinary action by a State Dental Council for`
  line `professional or ethical misconduct of registered dentist or professional and the`
  line `procedure for receiving complaints and grievances by Ethics and Dental Registration`
  line `Board under sub-section (4) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(zc) the act of commission or omission which amounts to professional or ethical`
  line `misconduct under clause (b) of the Explanation to section 29;`
  line
  line `(zd) other particulars to be contained in the National Register for Dentists under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(ze) the particulars to be contained in the National Register for Dental Auxiliaries`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(zf) the form, including the electronic form and the manner of maintaining the`
  line `National Registers, under sub-section (3) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(zg) the manner in which any name or qualification may be added to, or removed`
  line `from, the National Register and the grounds for removal thereof, under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(zh) the manner of entering the title, diploma or qualification in the State`
  line `Register or the National Register, under sub-section (3) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(zi) the period for which, and the manner in which, a foreign citizen who is`
  line `enrolled in his country as a dentist may be permitted temporary registration in India,`
  line `under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(zj) the manner of listing and maintaining dental qualifications granted by a`
  line `University or dental institution in India under sub-section (1) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(zk) the manner of examining the application for grant of recognition under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(zl) the manner of including a dental qualification in the list maintained by the`
  line `Board under sub-section (4) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(zm) the manner of preferring an appeal to the Commission for grant of`
  line `recognition under sub-section (5) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(zn) the manner of listing and maintaining dental qualifications which have been`
  line `granted recognition before the date of commencement of this Act under`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(zo) the designated authority for conducting Screening Test for higher dental`
  line `qualification, and the manner of conducting the Screening Test under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 34;`
  line
  line `(zp) the manner of listing and maintaining dental qualifications which have been`
  line `granted recognition before the date of commencement of this Act under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 34.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (83707)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83707&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every`
  line `regulation made, and every notification issued, under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions,`
  line `and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation`
  line `or notification or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation or notification should not be`
  line `made, the rule or regulation or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that`
  line `rule or regulation or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (83708)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83708&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of section 29 and section 48 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers under`
  line `sub-section (1), such rules may provide for the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salary and allowances payable to, and other conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members of the State Dental Council and Joint Dental Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of filling up of vacancies arising in the State Dental Council and Joint`
  line `Dental Council;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of State Legislature, where there are two Houses`
  line `and where there is one House of State Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (83709)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83709&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may`
  line `appear to it be necessary, for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of`
  line `two years from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (83710)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83710&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may`
  line `appoint in this behalf, the Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948) shall stand repealed and the`
  line `Dental Council of India constituted under section 3 of the said Act shall stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Act referred to in sub-section (1), it shall not`
  line affect,--
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the Act so repealed or anything duly done or suffered`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the`
  line `Act so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty incurred in respect of any contravention under the Act so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation,`
  line `liability, penalty as aforesaid, and any such proceeding or remedy may be instituted,`
  line `continued or enforced, and any such penalty may be imposed as if that Act had not been`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(3) On the dissolution of the Dental Council of India, the person acting as the President`
  line `and Members of the Dental Council of India holding office as such immediately before such`
  line `dissolution shall vacate their respective offices and such President and Members shall be`
  line `entitled to claim compensation not exceeding three months’ pay and allowances for the`
  line `premature termination of term of their office or of any contract of service.`
  line
  line `(4) Every officer who has been appointed on deputation basis in the Dental Council of`
  line `India shall, on its dissolution, stand reverted to his parent cadre, Ministry or Department, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) The services of other employees who have been, before the dissolution of the Dental`
  line `Council of India, employed on regular basis by the Dental Council of India, shall continue for no longer than one year after the commencement of this Act, as an interim arrangement`
  line `and thereafter, further continuity or otherwise of their services shall be determined by the`
  line `Commission on the basis of their performance appraisal or evaluation:`
  line
  line `Provided that such employees of the erstwhile Dental Council of India shall be entitled`
  line `to such compensation which shall not be less three months’ pay and allowances, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding the repeal of the aforesaid enactment, any order made, any licence`
  line `to practice issued, any registration made, any permission to start new dental college or to`
  line `start higher course of studies or for increase in the admission capacity granted, any`
  line `recognition of dental qualifications granted, under the Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948),`
  line `which are in force as on the date of commencement of this Act, shall continue to be in force`
  line `till the date of their expiry for all purposes, as if they had been issued or granted under the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (83711)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Transitory provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069&sectionId=83711&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_2023-21_1710130648069
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall be the successor in interest to`
  line `the Dental Council of India including its subsidiaries or owned trusts and all the assets and`
  line `liabilities of the Dental Council of India shall be deemed to have been transferred to the`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948), the educational`
  line `standards, requirements and other provisions of the said Act and the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder shall continue to be in force and operate till new standards or requirements`
  line `are specified under this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that anything done or any action taken as regards the educational standards and`
  line `requirements under the enactment under repeal and the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions`
  line `of this Act and shall continue in force accordingly unless and until superseded by anything`
  line `done or by any action taken under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Dentists Act, 1948 (16 of 1948), the State Council`
  line `and the Joint State Council constituted respectively under section 21 and section 23 of the`
  line `said Act shall continue to operate until a new State Dental Council is established by the`
  line `State Government in accordance with the provisions of section 29 of this Act.`
